bio.experienceSummary: I am a mother of 3 boys, a wife, and a teacher. I love children. They are my world. I have worked as an early childhood educator for the past 25 years and 2 years of experience as an educational assistant for elementary school. I am friendly, fun, and outgoing. I have good communication skills with children, and I'm able to connect with them quickly. I am an honest and one-time person with a big heart. My goal is to always help shape futures step by step

description.originalText: Very trustworthy, Honest, and caring. I love who she’s teaches and cares for mine.

bio.experienceSummary:
I enjoy working with kids because they are so fun to watch as they grow and learn about this world. I see their interests and knowledge expand every day. 

I'm looking for a job that meets the needs of the family and myself well. I would like to provide care while keeping my own 1-year-old with me. I am comfortable with caring for up to 5 - 6 children at a time. I have 4 children, though the older 3 are teens - young adults. I have also fostered, so I am used to having 5 - 6 kids in tow. 

I started working with kids when I was 13. I babysat throughout the entire summer, starting in middle school, and became a camp counselor in high school. After having my first child, I became a RN and started doing pediatric home care nursing, which I have done for the past 18 years. My specialty is caring for kids with disabilities and medical needs.

Hi I am Rosie and I am a rising Senior at Emory University in Atlanta and am home in Pennington for the summer. I am studying Anthropology and Psychology and have a 4. 0 GPA! I am a diver on the varsity swimming and diving team. I have nannied consistently since I was 15, have taught swim lessons for 4 summers, and am the head diving coach on the team for the second year. I love to play outdoors, be active, board games, and seeing kids learn and grow. I cannot wait to get to meet you and your family. My main goals are always a safe, fun, and healthy day!

I'm a dedicated, caring, and passionate caregiver with extensive experience in childcare, education, and recreation with all ages (infants-teenagers).

I'm CPR and First Aid certified, and I have a strong background in child development, ensuring that every child in my care receives the attention, love, and guidance they need to thrive. I'm known for being patient, responsible, and empathetic, always prioritizing children's safety and well-being.

I love outdoor games and encourage children to explore and learn through play.

My native language is Spanish, and while I'm continually improving my English, this has never been a barrier to providing the best care. In fact, I see it as a unique opportunity for children to be naturally exposed to a second language, enhancing their cognitive and language skills.

My priority is to create a warm and enriching environment where your child feels happy, safe, and supported. I would love the opportunity to be a positive influence in your family's

description.originalText: Stefany has been amazing in taking care of my 20-month-old baby. She is very fun and loving, always showing patience and affection. My little princess loves spending time with her, and it’s clear how much she adores her. I highly recommend her!

bio.experienceSummary: Hello! My name's Laura and I have 12 years of experience taking care of children, from infants all the way up to pre-teens. I'm currently working for a family that will be moving back to their home state in May of 2025. I have my own transportation and can assist in school/daycare pick-up and drop-off. I'm CPR/First Aid certified and a non-smoker. I'm more than willing to help out if you need any light housekeeping done. I'm also available for weekends and the odd weekday night if needed. I have references that I can provide upon request. If you have any questions please feel free to message me and I'll try to get back to you as soon as possible!

description.displayText: Laura is incredible, reliable and very responsible with the kids. Happy to provide more details!
description.originalText: Laura is incredible, reliable and very responsible with the kids. Happy to provide more details!

bio.experienceSummary:
I am a former special education teacher with 8+ years of nannying/childcare experience and 10 years of coaching experience. I have worked with children of all ages, from newborns to teenagers! I have experience with multiples, children with medical needs, children with behavioral needs, and children with disabilities! My background and passion for education mean I prioritize developmentally appropriate goals and activities. My experience is very broad, you name it, I've likely done it! 

My spouse and I have two dogs that we absolutely spoil! I love the outdoors, you can catch me hiking, swimming, or camping in my free time. I come from a BIG family so am very accustomed to organized chaos! I've been told that I come across as a very calm and collected person with a positive attitude. I strive to have a problem-solving mindset and am constantly thinking about the behavior I want to model for kids.

Call me Angie, I started my experience with childcare in my teens watching children of family friends. Before graduating high school, I nannied, tutored and fed dinner to three children: age 4, 10 and 14, for several years before I went to college. There I completed several education courses. Alongside college, I also worked at a nearby church as a Nursery care giver for 0 to 4 years olds. Then I graduated in 2013. A few years later I worked as administrator and pet sitter for Distinctive Petsitting, before getting into other administrative positions.

In my spare time, I like to make crafts. I do a large variety of crafts. I've done sewing, glass mosaics, candle making, pottery, gardening and whatever else I can try. 

One thing you should know about me is I believe childcare is one of the most important things and can be the hardest as well.

description.originalText: We hired Angie for picking up my son from school to variety of activities. She is very on time and responsible. She lets me know when she picked up and the ETA every time. We will continually have her as our helper for the rest of the school year.

bio.experienceSummary: My name is Marva and I have been working with children for over 25 years. I have 3 grown daughters and 4 grandchildren. Also worked with infants and Toddlers inside my home and Daycare Facilities. I enjoy reading, singing songs and doing arts and crafts and yes helping with potty training. I love teaching child life skills like manners and sharing . I love working with 0-5-year-old cause it is never a dull moment!!!

description.originalText:
Ms Marva has worked with us for over a month as a full-time nanny caring for my 3-year-old and my baby.  She is obviously passionate about what she does.  She has been consistently on time, responsible, and reliable.  She has engaged my son in learning - colors, numbers, words, days, months, and Spanish. No joke within 1 week, Ms Marva had the 9-month-old falling asleep and staying asleep in her crib, which had been a struggle - she is a baby whisperer.
The best part? Ms Marva likes to have fun - singing, dancing, reading books, being silly, playing games.  Incorporating fun is so important for my kids - and she keeps up with the wild 3-year-old. Ms Marva is like family and has become an important figure in our lives.  I trust her very much. I'm happy to recommend Ms Marva without any reservation.

bio.experienceSummary: I am a 26-year-old college student majoring in Communications. I have many years of child care experience from children of all ages! I have always had a passion for children and would love the opportunity to become a part of your families lives. I look forward to hearing from you soon.

description.originalText:
Ansley is an absolute gem! Not only have we relied on her countless times to watch my sister's kids, who always ask for her to stay forever but I’ve also had the pleasure of working with her as a personal assistant for my business. Ansley excels at time management and has made my life so much easier, allowing me to breathe and focus on the bigger picture. She is a significant reason why my business has been so successful.

I consider Ansley my right-hand person and often wish I could have a “mini her” by my side at all times! She has excelled in every aspect of her role, tackling a variety of tasks with ease. Ansley is incredibly easy to talk to and has a sweet, bubbly, personable, and caring demeanor that makes her adaptable to any environment.

She is both professional and highly skilled in childcare. There’s no doubt in my mind that Ansley would be a perfect addition to any business or household, leaving it better than she found it.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi there! I'm a passionate childcare provider who loves helping kids learn, grow, and thrive. With two years of experience, I feel confident caring for up to two children of different ages, and I always bring my creative and friendly energy to every interaction. Seeing kids smile and having fun together is one of the best parts of what I do!

I believe open and honest communication with parents is key, so I'm happy to keep you updated however works best for you-whether that's through texts, calls, or a quick chat at the end of the day. I also make it a priority to follow household rules, understanding how important structure and consistency are for kids.

From playing outdoor sports and physical games to enjoying board games, puzzles, and creative activities, I love finding fun, engaging ways to keep kids active and learning. With a college degree and coursework in early child development, I bring both knowledge and hands-on experience to nurturing every part of a child's growth.

description.originalText: My daughter had a great time and wouldn't stop raving the activities Toni had prepared.
